[6] Pakistan (Sindh)
Date: Wed 26 Jun 2013
Source: The Frontier Post, Pakistan Press International (PPI) report [edited]
http://www.thefrontierpost.com/article/22681/


As many as 43 measles cases have been reported in Sindh [province] in the month of June [2013], said Director Public Health on Wednesday [26 Jun 2013].

According to Director Public Health, 24 out of the 43 cases of measles, reported in Sindh province in June [2013], were reported in Mirpurkhas, 7 in Jamshoro, 5 in Badin, 4 in Dadu, 2 in Tando Muhammad Khan and one in Umerkot.

He said that one measles patient died in June [2013].

