The Americas
------------
[7] Canada (Ontario)
Date: Wed 26 Jul 2013
Source: The Hamilton Spectator [edited]
http://www.thespec.com/news-story/3858437-another-measles-case-found-in-burlington/


Halton Region is on alert for measles cases after a secondary case was reported in Burlington this week. The latest adult with measles had been in contact in a health-care setting with a person who had been reported with measles on 17 Jun 2013, said Halton's Medical Officer of Health, Dr. Bob Nosal. The new case is the only known secondary case to date, and the health department is now on watch for any additional cases, said Nosal. The new case may have led to additional exposures in Burlington.

If you think you may have measles, the health department advises calling ahead to the doctor's office, walk-in clinic or emergency department. Symptoms of the highly contagious virus include fever, cough, runny nose, red eyes and a rash. It is normally spread by coughing and sneezing and close personal contact.

--
